text: The Finnish Church (, ) is a church building in Gamla stan in the town of Stockholm in Sweden. It belongs to the Stockholm Finnish Parish of the Church of Sweden. The church was opened in 1725. It is located in what once was Lilla Bollhuset before it was rebuilt into a church. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:Church of Sweden churches Category:Churches in Stockholm Category:18th-century buildings and structures
title: Finnish Church, Stockholm
